The paper deals with the problem of person re-identification, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a method that uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) to generate unlabeled samples for semi-supervised learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a label smoothing regularization method, which is related to regularization techniques used in machine learning, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The use of GANs for sample generation involves deep learning techniques, which are covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of large-scale datasets, which is related to multimedia analysis and retrieval, covered in cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of fine-grained bird recognition, which is related to image retrieval, covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
